# Milo product help (RAG) — keep in sync with the app

When you add or materially change **owner-visible** consumer behavior (new routes, renamed Settings items, new flows such as transfers, family access, messages, health uploads, booking, journal, etc.), treat **Milo’s documentation RAG** as part of the same change unless the work is purely internal/refactor with no user-facing difference.

## Do this as part of the feature PR

1. **`docs/pawbuck-product-help/`** — Add or edit the Markdown article(s) for the flow (steps, screen names, limitations). Keep [`docs/pawbuck-product-help/INVENTORY.md`](../../docs/pawbuck-product-help/INVENTORY.md) in sync so coverage stays auditable.
2. **Starter chips** — If users should discover the feature from Milo’s suggested prompts, add or reorder a line in [`apps/consumer-app/constants/productHelpStarters.ts`](../../apps/consumer-app/constants/productHelpStarters.ts) (short “How do I …?” strings).
3. **Re-embed** — After merging copy changes, run the seed script so `public.documentation` matches (staging/prod per your process). See [`docs/MILO_RAG.md`](../../docs/MILO_RAG.md):

   `cd apps/consumer-app && npx tsx scripts/seed-documentation-rag.ts --env-file .env.local`

4. **Tests** — If you change prompt-building logic, extend [`apps/consumer-app/__tests__/services/miloSuggestedPrompts.test.ts`](../../apps/consumer-app/__tests__/services/miloSuggestedPrompts.test.ts) (or relevant API tests).

## When you can skip

- Pure copy/theme tweaks that do not change **where** or **how** users do something.
- Provider app–only or backend-only changes with **no** consumer navigation or Milo-facing behavior change.

